Ida Sniffen Walters was the central figure in a sad case in which she poisoned her two children and attempted to kill herself in December, 1912 in New York.  She was the mistress of a prominent New York lawyer <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/7118544861/"><img src="http://farm9.staticflickr.com/8151/7118544861_929cc07cf9_m.jpg" width="165" height="240" alt="Lorlys E. Rogers (LOC)" /></a>who stood by her, divorced his wife, and married her in prison.  Suffering from what we would probably call profound, post-partum depression, she was found insane.
